<H1 ALIGN="CENTER">The Holy City of Kashi</H1>
        
        Varanasi, also commomly known as <b> Benaras </b>or<b> Banaras </b> is 
        one of the oldest cities in the world situated on the west bank of the 
        holy River Ganga (Ganges) and is regarded as holy by Hindus, Buddhists 
        and Jains. The city is believed to be about 3000 years old. According to 
        <b>legend</b>, the city was founded by the <b>Hindu</b> deity, <b>Lord Shiva</b>
        , around 5000 years ago thus making it as one of the most important 
        pilgrimage destinations in the country.
        
